cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper presents a tool for automatic generation of substation one-line diagrams, which is a software engineering task.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the tool uses algorithms to automatically compute the coordinates of all components and generate the substation one-line diagram.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the tool is used for energy management system applications and power system control.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the tool may involve programming languages and techniques for developing the automatic generation algorithm.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the tool is used for power system engineering and planning.
